-- Iran Detains 6,000 Foreigners, Mostly Illegal Aliens, Mehr Says
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2012-03-11T09:52:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/iran-detains-6-000-foreigners-mostly-illegal-aliens-mehr-says.html
Iranian authorities have detained
about 6,000 foreigners, Mehr reported, citing Mohammad Tahouri,
managing director of the Bureau for Aliens and Foreign
Immigrants’ Affairs.  Most of these detainees are illegal immigrants, Tahouri
said, according to the  report  published today by the state-run
 news agency . Mehr gave no time frame for the detentions.  “They have been arrested by Iranian police mostly for
charges such as drug trafficking and murder,” he said,
according to Mehr.  The Persian Gulf state is home to more than 1.5 million
illegal immigrants, the news agency reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
